    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-08-07T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-08-07T18:00:00-05:00" n="115"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d115">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72119/10</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_PWH1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Page</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                    <placeName>
                        <hi rend="italic">London</hi>
                    </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-08-07T23:00:00+00:00">
                        <hi rend="italic">August 7, 1914, 11 p.m.</hi>
                    </date>
                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received August 8, 5 a.m.</hi>] </dateline>
                <p rend="center">[Telegram]</p>
                <p>299. Your August 5, 11 a.m.<note n="1" xml:id="d115fn1">see footnote, <hi
                            rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_42">p. 42</ref>.</note> I have
                    delivered directly to the King the message of the President. His Majesty
                    expressed most earnestly his thanks and requested me to convey them to the
                    President. He talked long and appreciatively and he expressed the hope that an
                    occasion would come when the President’s offer of mediation might be
                    accepted.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_PWH1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Page</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
